18/12/2002
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The National Commission for Integration into NATO convened Tuesday (17 December) to present a report on ongoing accession negotiations. 
State Secretary Mihnea Motoc said that the foreign ministry held the first round of talks on 13 December in Brussels and assumed political and military obligations under several enlargement documents. 
The second round of negotiations, scheduled for 9 January, will focus on legislative and information security aspects.
In other news, President Ion Iliescu's office announced on Tuesday that he will support the government-sponsored package for fighting corruption. 
Iliescu will urge all state institutions to send strong signals against corruption and has asked parliament to adopt legislative reforms proposed by the government. 
(Rompres, Nine O'Clock, NATO website - 18/12/02)
